tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE clean_up_efforts (
  clean_up_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  location_id UUID,
  date DATE,
  organizer VARCHAR,
  debris_type VARCHAR,
  debris_quantity INT
);

CREATE TABLE clean_up_efforts (
 id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
 location VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
 date DATE NOT NULL,
 debris_type VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE volunteer_records (
 id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
 name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
 email VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
 phone_number VARCHAR(15) NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE debris_types (
 id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
 type_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
 description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE clean_up_logs (
 id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
 clean_up_id INT REFERENCES clean_up_efforts(id),
 volunteer_id INT REFERENCES volunteer_records(id),
 debris_collected INT
)

CREATE TABLE debris_clean_up_efforts (
	id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	location VARCHAR(255),
	date DATE,
	volunteers INT
)

CREATE TABLE debris_types (
	id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	type_name VARCHAR(255),
	description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE clean_up_teams (
	id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	team_name VARCHAR(255),
	eam_lead VARCHAR(255),
	eam_size INT
)

CREATE TABLE clean_up_reports (
	id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	clean_up_id INT,
	eam_id INT,
eport_date DATE,
eport_text TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE debris_collection_points (
	id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	eam_id INT,
	ype_id INT,
	ime_spent_hours INT,
	rash_collected_kg FLOAT
)
